We have been wanting to enter in structured data to Confluence pages for quite some time. The closest we have found to doing this is the Page_Properties macro which if looked at closely has enabled key_value pairs to be entered in per page.

We would like Atalassian to enhance Page_Properties to behave like page Labels. So when a Page_Property Row is created the first column would search known Labels, allowing autocompletion. When the second column (the value) is entered then autocompletion would occur for that key_value. All keys and their corresponding value sets could then be managed as Labels are currently managed. The Page_Properties_Reporting layer would be enhanced to allow export/import via Excel or restful interfaces.

(Note: in the document attached I've used the term 'Tag' instead of 'Label'

